nodes.text: The Street of Glory was a street within Naboo's capital city of Theed that led close to Theed Royal Palace. In 32 BBY, while Theed was occupied by the Trade Federation Droid Army, an abandoned building on the Street of Glory was used as a prison to house several of Naboo's citizens, including Minister of Culture Kyu Tane and his wife. The prisoners were eventually sprung by members of the Naboo Underground.
